-- Kolon Industries shares rally after a U.S. court ruling on DuPont case 
-- By Hyunjoo Jin
-- Thu Apr 03, 2014 08:14PM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, April 4 (Reuters) - Shares of Kolon Industries Inc <120110.KS> surged by the daily limit of 15 percent on Friday after a U.S. federal appeals court threw out a $919.9 million jury verdict against the South Korean  company. [ID:nL1N0MV18T]

On Thursday, the 4th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals in Richmond, Virginia, voided the September 2011 verdict that favoured DuPont Co <DD.N> over the alleged theft of its trade secrets related to a fibre used to make Kevlar bulletproof vests.